    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, an escrow account, you say? Well, imagine you're a wise old wizard, and you've just agreed to trade your magical staff for a shiny new sword. But before you can hand over your staff, you need a trustworthy goblin to hold onto it until the sword is delivered and the magic is transferred. That's what an escrow account is like in the world of house buying. It's a secure place where your money is kept safe, like a goblin's treasure chest, until all the conditions of the house purchase are met. Once everything is in order, the goblin releases your gold to the seller, and the sword—er, house—is yours. It's a way to ensure that both parties play fair and no one gets tricked by goblins or goblin-like schemes. So, in short, an escrow account is a magical safeguard for your hard-earned gold during the house-buying quest.",
