    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Apologies for the confusion. An escrow account is a financial arrangement where a third party holds and regulates payment of the funds required for two parties involved in a given transaction. In the context of buying a condo in Toronto, the escrow account serves as a neutral holding place for your money. This ensures that the funds are available to pay for the condo once all the agreed-upon conditions are met, such as inspections, appraisals, and the signing of the purchase agreement.\n\nThe escrow account helps to protect both the buyer and the seller. For the buyer, it ensures that their money is safe and will only be released when the terms of the sale are fulfilled. For the seller, it provides assurance that the buyer's funds will be available when needed. The escrow company acts as a trusted intermediary, releasing funds to the seller only when the buyer's conditions are met, and releasing funds to the buyer only when the seller's conditions are met.\n\nIn summary, an escrow account is a secure way to handle the exchange of funds during a real estate transaction, ensuring that both parties are protected and that the transaction proceeds smoothly.",
